      "id": "PopularPost284012",
      "post_content": "The old philosophy behind card design was: \"We can't make this too cheap -- it will swing games.\" As if *swinging games* was a bad thing. Why play a card if it won't gain you an advantage and help swing the game in your favor? That erroneous philosophy made many cards of this era -- like this one -- totally unplayable.",
